result.formatted_address: 26～28 Morrison Hill Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: New Ka Mei Restaurant

reviews.text: The food was very yummy, went for dinner and had to go back for lunch!

The food served in this restaurant is delicious, except for salads. Salad ingredients are not made with fresh potatoes but with canned fruits. This is very bad, so it is not recommended. Other dishes are of good quality, especially its set lunch. A set lunch including meals and drinks costs about HK$50. The price is reasonable. In addition, the restaurant also serves bread, cakes and desserts. Good quality. The dessert is a French caramel stewed egg, very delicious.

Fast, cheap(er), cheerful local place. They're willing to customise your order and friendly with kids The evening duty lady speaks English and is very accommodating. Be tempted by the creme caramel and variety of panna cotta (I know, right). Fried rice, sweet and sour fish and charred long beans were particularly delicious. Breakfast was basic caff fare.
nice food, one of my favorite cha chan ten
Very local and friendly staff, foods are great. If you want to try local foods and experience a kind of local community, this would be an ideal candidate.

reviews.text: 食早餐，雞翼加煎蛋通粉，熱檸茶($36)。雞翼超唔得，無味道，無任何調味，齋炸～超難食
我比新嘉美餐廳，分數是66分至70分，原因價錢經濟，碟頭大，味道都ok合格，最重耍位置非常好，交通方便，巴士站集中，咁情况值得推介，GOODGOODOk。
地方清潔，㕑房夠鑊氣，好食
The food was very yummy, went for dinner and had to go back for lunch!
